# GDScript Patterns

## Folder Structure — By System

Each system owns all its files in one folder. Never scatter a system across multiple folders.

```
scripts/core/        # Shared infrastructure — no game knowledge (MeshTransformer, ModelAssembler, MeshBuilder, interactable base)
scripts/player/      # CharacterBody3D, PlayerSession autoload
scripts/ship/        # BoatBody, controller, camera, propulsion, ShipBuilder
scripts/ocean/       # FftWaterSystem, WaveSurface
scripts/weather/     # WorldWeather + WeatherLighting autoloads, WeatherState, WeatherZone
scripts/time/        # WorldClock autoload
scripts/world/       # World, ProximityLoader, WorldRenderer, AtmosphericEffects
scripts/port/        # PortPlot, PortDock, PortFacilities, buildings, PortData
scripts/npc/         # NpcBase, HarbourMasterNpc, ShipwrightNpc, ContractNpc, DeliveryNpc
scripts/cargo/       # ContractRegistry autoload, Contract, CargoItem, CargoPickup, Warehouse
scripts/ui/          # GameMenu + DebugHud autoloads, HUDs, overlays
scripts/state/       # GameState autoload, PlayerState, ShipState, ContractState, WorldState
```

## Actual Autoloads

These are the registered singletons. Do not reference anything else as if it were an autoload.

| Autoload | Role |
|---|---|
| `WorldWeather` | Wind, rain, fog state and weather zones |
| `WeatherLighting` | Sky colour, fog, sun angle |
| `WorldClock` | Game time |
| `ContractRegistry` | Port registry, contracts, commodities |
| `PlayerSession` | Player marks and persistence |
| `GameMenu` | Pause / menu |
| `GameState` | Read model — player, ship, contract, world sub-states |
| `DebugHud` | F3 debug overlay |

A scene that needs port data asks `ContractRegistry`, not its own parent. A HUD that needs ship speed reads `GameState.ship.speed_knots`, not a ship node.

## State Model — UI Reads GameState

```gdscript
# BAD — polling a scene node
var speed = $Ship.velocity.length()

# GOOD — read model
var speed = GameState.ship.speed_knots
```

Systems write their own state. GameState aggregates sub-states. UI subscribes to GameState.

## Jigsaw Components — No Reaching Up

Nodes communicate across system boundaries via signals or autoloads, not node paths.

```gdscript
# BAD
get_parent().get_parent().get_node("HUD").show_prompt(text)

# GOOD — signal out
signal interaction_triggered(context: Dictionary)

# GOOD — autoload
ContractRegistry.get_contracts_for_port(port_id)
```

## Ship Building — Templates Not Scenes

New ships are built from JSON templates, not hand-placed scenes. Never manually add ship components in the editor.

```gdscript
var boat := ShipBuilder.build("res://resources/data/ships/fuel_tanker.json")
get_tree().current_scene.add_child(boat)
boat.place_at_waterline(water_y)
```

Hull orientation: **Bow = +Z, Stern = −Z, Port = −X, Starboard = +X.**
Hull parts always use `"rotation_degrees": [0, -90, 0]`. Never add extra rotation.

## Interactable Pattern

All "press E to do thing" logic inherits from `interactable.gd` in `scripts/core/`.
Do not hand-roll prompt display or interaction detection per object.

## Data-Driven

Port definitions, ship templates, commodity configs → `resources/data/`. Scripts read from data.

```gdscript
# BAD
var exports = ["grain", "timber"]

# GOOD
var port_data := ContractRegistry.get_port_data(port_id)
var exports   := port_data.commodity_export
```
